a\) Transparent Statistical Methods

In part 1 they used a logical regression. They are comparing a binary variable and a continous variable. In part 2 they are using a chi-square test, measuring the association between two variables.

b\) Suggestions for Rewriting

Part 1:

American Avocets are more likely to use micro habitats at certain distances from the edge of the water. Thus proving that the distance to the water edge influences habitat use patterns.

Part 2:

Different bird species differ in their habitat. American Avocets, Foster's Terns, and Black necked Stilits all show different habitat preferences across wetlands.

c\) Further Analysis

An additional variable that may be influencing the American Avocet micro habitat use is the water depth. This is a continuous variable that is measuring depth by centimeters using a meter stick. Depth of water may affect the availability of food for the birds. Eating a variety of aquatic animals, the depth of water will heavily affect their ability to catch food and the presence of food in general.

