k\) Figure one showed that all three species of ants mostly nest around 200cm and have a probability of nest occupancy of about 1.00. Both BBR and AB have a predicted probability of 1.000 at 600cm, this is because they are more aggressive species. RRB has a probability of 0.9841796. They have a lower probability because they are less aggressive. The logistic regression model indicated that both tree height and ant species influence the nest occurrence. Trees occupied by less aggressive ants tend to have more nests. This occurs because some acacia ants aggressively defend their habitat by attacking birds.

